The software was parameterized to identify 4 functional phytoplankton populations: \textit{Crocosphaera}, Picoeukaryotes, \textit{Prochlorococcus}, and \textit{Synechococcus}.  \Sexpr{missing_memo}  Picoeukaryotes and \textit{Prochlorococcus} are identified by fsc\_small and chl\_small while \textit{Synechococcus} and \textit{Crocosphaera} are identified by pe vs. fsc\_small. Yellow-green 1 $\mu$m polystyrene beads are identified as a cohesive population with high pe and fsc\_small.  Particles that are not identified as one of these phytoplankton groups or beads are designated "unknown" (Fig. \ref{fig:phyP_class}).

